AS PASSED SENATE
A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Article 1 of Chapter 34 of Title 43 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated,
2 relating to Georgia Composite Medical Board, so as to provide for the board to implement
3 an automated licensing system for certain healthcare providers in this state; to provide for
4 requirements; to provide for related matters; to repeal conflicting laws; and for other
5 purposes.
6 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
7 SECTION 1.
8 Article 1 of Chapter 34 of Title 43 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to
9 Georgia Composite Medical Board, is amended in Code Section 43-34-6, relating to board
10 as an independent agency, by adding new subsections to read as follows:
11 "(k) No later than October 1, 2025, the board shall implement a data management software
12 system to streamline and automate the licensing process for physicians, physician
13 assistants, and anesthesiologist assistants. No later than January 1, 2026, such system shall
14 be fully operational for other healthcare providers licensed by the board.
15 (l) The system provided for in subsection (k) of this Code section may:
