16 (1) Organize, verify, and store the licenses of healthcare providers, allowing for a single
17 verification process that results in authorization state wide, provided that a healthcare
18 facility, licensee, or applicant inputs the credentialing information and agrees to such
19 authorization;
20 (2) If available, be customizable so that a healthcare facility can add requirements to
21 meet such facility's rules, regulations, or bylaws;
22 (3) Provide a public facing page that is easily and securely accessible by other state
23 medical boards, healthcare providers, and healthcare facilities;
24 (4) Notify any individual submitting credentials into such system when his or her
25 application is deficient, what such deficiency is, and when such application is complete;
26 (5) Process complete applications within 30 days and process reappointments within two
27 weeks;
28 (6) Provide for the registration of nurse protocol agreements for advanced practice
29 registered nurses and job descriptions for licensed physician assistants and
30 anesthesiologist assistants;
31 (7) Allow any healthcare facility to accept the information for licensing as acceptance
32 for credentialing and any healthcare provider to add additional requirements for
33 credentialing in their facility; and
34 (8) Perform any other functions the board deems necessary to improve licensing
35 processes under this chapter."
36 SECTION 2.
37 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
